@Node Description "Description"

  Description
  ===========

    Frontend is first door called that the user sees.  It is called by @{"AwaitConnect" link HBBS:Docs/Doors/AwaitConnect.guide/MAIN}

    The door does this:

    * Asks for system and node password and display PrivateSystem and
      PrivateNode special screens as appropriate.

    * To ask user for their Handle

    * Check the user name is in the userdatabase
      - if not then call new user door

    * Ask user for their password.

    * Check password is correct.
      - if not then call hack door

    * Fill in N_ND->User with the correct data.

    * Check if user is allowed to logon
      - Access Level >= N_ND->AccessRequired ?
      - Allowed at this time ?

    * Reset user->TimeUsed to 0 if last called date is not the same
      as today's date.

    * return one of the following strings.
      - LOGGEDIN
      - HACK
      - FAILED

    * Check to see if there is an access level the same as the user, if not
      flag the sysop and downgrade the user's access level to the next lowest one.

@EndNode


