@Node ScreensDisplayed "Screens Displayed"

  Screens Displayed
  =================

    PrivateSystem - Before the user sees anything else.
                    If this screen is present then the user will be prompted
                    for a system password defined in the NodeLocal/NodeGlobal
                    config files.

    PrivateNode   - If this is displayed the user is asked for a Node password
                    defined in NodeLocal/NodeGlobal

    Speed_<Baud>  - Just after node password

    BBStitle      - Just before the login prompt.

@EndNode

@Node DoorsCalled "Doors Called"

  Doors Called
  ============

    System Doors:

    NEWUSER <Username>
    HACK [TIME|PSWD|LOCK]

@EndNode

@Node Returns "Returns"

  Returned Values (in N_ND->DoorReturn)
  =====================================

    LOGGEDIN - If user is correctly logged in.
    HACK     - If a hack attempt was made.
    FAILED   - Otherwise (e.g. carrier loss)

@EndNode


@Node ConfigFiles "ConfigFiles"

  Config Files
  ============

    Progdir:FrontEnd.CFG
    --------------------

      HandleToShortMsg    - Message displayed to user on short handle entry
      NameCorrectMsg      - Message displayed to user verification of
                            correctly entered name if account is not present.
      InvalidHandleMsg    - Message displayed upon invalid handle
      HangupCommand       - if the user types this command at the name prompt
                            a hangup will be forced.
      PromptTimeout       - determines the amount of time that's waited for a
                            username or password to be entered before they are
                            prompted again.
      MaxAttempts         - determines the amount of attempts a user gets at
                            entering a handle.
      AlreadyLoggedInMsg  - Message displayed to user if they're already
                            logged in
      NamesNotAllowed_XX  - List of handles that arenot allowed.
                            Defaults To:

                              NamesNotAllowed_1=SYSOP

                            Further examples:

                              NamesNotAllowed_1=SYSOP
                              NamesNotAllowed_2=ALL
                              NamesNotAllowed_3=EALL
                              NamesNotAllowed_4=Everybody
                              NamesNotAllowed_5=Wanker

      HandleNotAllowedMsg - Displayed when the user enters an handle that
                            appears in the NamesNotAllowed list

      UseSpecialScreens   - Use SpecialScreen files instead of text messages
                            for errors.

                            e.g. say you set HandleToShortMsg=HTSHORT the
                            special screen HTSHORT will be displayed instead
                            of a message.

                            This allows complete customization of the frontend
                            door!

@EndNode

